    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Barriers that surround a camp or settlement, or reinforce a defensive wall. They are typically composed of strong branches of trees placed upon a rampart, or they are made of a palisaded bank or mound, or a rampart of earth, sod, or stones.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
